==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Entellus
<hw>En*tel"lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., the
specific name, fr. Gr. <?/ to command.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>
<def>An East Indian long-tailed bearded monkey (<spn>Semnopithecus
entellus</spn>) regarded as sacred by the natives. It is remarkable for
the caplike arrangement of the hair on the head. Called also
<altname>hoonoomaun</altname> and <altname>hungoor</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Entend</ent>⟦br⟧
